\pard\f0\fs28   {\b 13. O. majorii} Beauverd,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Genève }ser. 2, {\b 6}: 152 (1914). Plant up to 150 cm. Stem whitish-arachnoid-hairy; wings up to 8 mm wide, triangular-acuminate, with 3- to 5-palmate spines, with apical spine up to 15 mm. Leaves up to 45 × 15 cm, lanceolate, sessile, pinnatisect or almost pinnate, greyish-green, sparsely hairy and glandular above, densely greyish-tomentulose beneath; lobes triangular-acute, deeply lobulate, with apical spine up to 10 mm. Capitula 45-50 × 70-80 mm, hemispherical, glabrous; involucral bracts 5-8 mm wide at base, the outer and middle deflexed, with wide fimbriate-spiny apex, the apical spine up to 10 mm, caudate, the other spines 1-3 mm. Corolla 35-50 mm, purple. Achenes 6-7 mm; pappus 9-14 mm.{\i  Karpathos, E. Kriti.} Cr.
